      "writtenOn": "2017-04-11T17:43:55Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Since there’s no real reason that data_size should ever be 0, and we’d wind up in undefined behavior territory with this implementation if it ever was 0, #include \"base/logging.h\" DCHECK_NE(data_size, 0u).\n\nAlternatively, tolerate 0 by skipping the memcpy() if that’s what data_size is. Then you’ve also got to change the call to ExtensionStreamDataSourceRead() to give nullptr instead of data_.data() if data_.size() is 0.\n\nIt actually may be worth accepting the 0 and having a test for zero-length extension streams in (perhaps) minidump_file_writer_test.cc, since the MinidumpUserExtensionStreamDataSource says that zero-length streams are OK.",
      "revId": "64dbce024da61769a7e276a9ebc279b3c1f5251f",
